Cheesy Chicken and Broccoli Soup
  --JEssica Rudolph, Cook's Country
  
3 tbsp unsalted butter
1 onion, chopped fine
1 1/4 tsp table salt
1 tsp pepper
2 tbsp ap flour
3 c chicken broth
2 (6-8 oz) boneless, skinless chicken breasts, trimmed and halved lengthwise
1 lb broccoli florets, cut into 1/2" pieces
1 c heavy cream
8 oz sharp cheddar cheese, shredded (2 c)
4 oz American cheese, chopped (1 c)

Melt butter in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add onion, salt, and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~4 min Add flour and cook, stirring to coat onion, ~1 min. Gradually whisk in broth. Add chicken and broccoli and bring to simmer. Cover; reduce heat to medium-low; and simmer until chicken registers 160 F, ~10 min. Transfer chicken to plate and shred into bite-size pieces using 2 forks. Stir cream into soup and return to simmer over medium heat. Whisk in cheddar and American cheese until melted, ~2 min. Stir in chicken. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve.

